In this speech, President Biden expresses gratitude for his local fire department in Wilmington, Delaware, who saved his life when he had a cranial aneurysm. He also shares a personal story about how the firefighters saved his home and his wife's life during a fire. The President acknowledges the bravery and dedication of firefighters, stating that they are willing to run towards danger while others run away. He emphasizes the importance of having more firefighters to protect communities and announces funding initiatives to support firefighters, including grants for salaries, equipment, and cancer research. The President concludes by thanking the firefighters and their families for their sacrifices and promises to continue supporting them.